{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:24:58.578Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the official Claude Cookbook and Claude API course documentation, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Parallelization\""},{"type":"text","text":" is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multi-LLM workflow pattern that distributes independent subtasks across multiple LLMs for concurrent processing"},{"type":"text","text":", then aggregates the results."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The parallelization workflow takes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"one task and breaks it into multiple subtasks"},{"type":"text","text":", runs them "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"all at the same time (concurrently)"},{"type":"text","text":", then "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"joins all results together in a final aggregator step"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Basic Flow"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Main Task → Split into N Subtasks\n    ↓\n[N Parallel LLM calls run simultaneously]\n    ↓\n[Subtask 1 output] [Subtask 2 output] [Subtask 3 output] ...\n    ↓\nAggregator (Claude combines all results)\n    ↓\nFinal Output"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pattern follows a clear sequence:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Happens"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Break into subtasks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decompose one task into multiple independent subtasks"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run in parallel"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Launch all N subtasks simultaneously (same time)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specialized prompts"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each subtask has a prompt specialized for that particular sub-problem"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Collect results"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gather outputs from all parallel subtasks"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aggregator step"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Feed all results to Claude for final synthesis/recommendation"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Material Suitability Analysis"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- User submits: Image of a part\n- Break into 4 subtasks: \"Is metal good for this part?\", \"Is polymer good?\", \"Is ceramic good?\", \"Is composite good?\"\n- Run 4 parallel Claude requests with specialized prompts for each material\n- Aggregator step: Claude combines all 4 results and gives final material recommendation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation in Claude Code: Task Tool with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"run_in_background"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude Code uses the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task tool"},{"type":"text","text":" to spawn parallel subagents:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"javascript"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// CRITICAL: ALL Task calls MUST be in SINGLE assistant message for true parallelism\nI'm launching N parallel subagents:\n[Task 1]\ndescription: \"Subagent A - [purpose]\"\nprompt: \"[detailed instructions]\"\nrun_in_background: true\n\n[Task 2]\ndescription: \"Subagent B - [purpose]\"\nprompt: \"[detailed instructions]\"\nrun_in_background: true\n\n[Task 3]\ndescription: \"Subagent C - [purpose]\"\nprompt: \"[detailed instructions]\"\nrun_in_background: true"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Critical Rule"},{"type":"text","text":": ALL Task calls must be in a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single assistant message"},{"type":"text","text":" for true parallelism. If in separate messages, they run sequentially."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"After launching, retrieve results:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"javascript"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"TaskOutput: task_1_id\nTaskOutput: task_2_id\nTaskOutput: task_3_id"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use It"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallelization is ideal when:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Condition"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Parallelization Helps"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Subtasks are independent"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No task depends on another's output"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tasks target different files/concerns"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can run simultaneously without conflicts"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Need to focus on one task at a time"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prevents Claude from getting confused by considering multiple pros/cons simultaneously"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Want to improve/evaluate prompts easily"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each subtask has its own specialized prompt"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Need to scale well"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can add additional subtasks without subtracting from others"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Good candidates"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Multiple independent analyses (code review, security, tests)\n- Multi-file processing where files are independent\n- Exploratory tasks with different perspectives\n- Verification tasks with different checks\n- Feature implementation with independent components"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Avoid parallelization when"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Tasks have dependencies (Task B needs Task A's output)\n- Sequential workflows required (commit → push → PR)\n- Tasks modify the same files (risk of conflicts)\n- Order matters for correctness"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallelization Patterns"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern 1: Task-Based Parallelization"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plan:\n1. Implement auth module\n2. Create API endpoints\n3. Add database schema\n4. Write unit tests\n5. Update documentation\n\nSpawn 5 subagents (one per task):\n- Subagent 1: Implements auth module\n- Subagent 2: Creates API endpoints\n- Subagent 3: Adds database schema\n- Subagent 4: Writes unit tests\n- Subagent 5: Updates documentation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern 2: Perspective-Based Parallelization"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perspectives: Security, Performance, Testing, Architecture\n\nSpawn 4 subagents:\n- Subagent 1: Security review\n- Subagent 2: Performance analysis\n- Subagent 3: Test coverage review\n- Subagent 4: Architecture assessment"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern 3: Parallel File Processing"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"tasks = [\n  \"Refactor src/controllers/user.ts to async/await\",\n  \"Refactor src/controllers/product.ts to async/await\",\n  \"Refactor src/controllers/order.ts to async/await\"\n]\n# Launch all 3 simultaneously"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance Benefits"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Approach"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5 Tasks @ 30s each"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Total Time"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sequential"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"30s + 30s + 30s + 30s + 30s"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"~150s"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 5 run simultaneously"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"~30s"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel execution is approximately "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Nx faster where N is the number of independent tasks"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Real-world performance"},{"type":"text","text":":\n| Task | Sequential | Parallel | Reduction |\n|------|------------|----------|-----------|\n| Research + Implementation | 45min | 18min | 60%↓ |\n| Test generation (5 files) | 30min | 10min | 67%↓ |\n| Documentation | 20min | 7min | 65%↓ |"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-3x throughput improvement in practice."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Use It (3 Key Benefits)"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explanation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Focus on one task at a time"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude won't get confused/distraught considering all pros/cons simultaneously"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Easy to improve/evaluate prompts"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each subtask has its own specialized prompt you can tune independently"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scales very well"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can add additional subtasks without subtracting from other subtasks"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of parallelization like a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"restaurant kitchen"},{"type":"text","text":": instead of one chef doing everything sequentially (prep → cook → plate), you have 3 chefs working simultaneously (one preps, one cooks, one plates). Then the head chef combines all the work into the final dish."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallelization distributes independent subtasks across multiple LLMs for concurrent processing"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Break one task into N subtasks → run all simultaneously → aggregate results"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each subtask has a specialized prompt for that particular sub-problem"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Final aggregator step combines all results into unified output"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In Claude Code: use Task tool with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"run_in_background: true"},{"type":"text","text":" in single message"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ALL Task calls must be in ONE assistant message for true parallelism"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subtasks must be independent — no task depends on another's output"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel execution is Nx faster where N = number of independent tasks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade cost/latency for improved performance — parallelization multiplies token usage proportionally"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"One of three basic multi-LLM patterns: Prompt Chaining, Parallelization, Routing"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices"},{"type":"text","text":": Use Haiku for lightweight tasks (1/6 cost), keep parallel count ≤ 5, Haiku for research/Sonnet for implementation."}]}]}}
